Remove the @unsalted butter{30%g} from the fridge to allow it to soften slightly.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the
@pre-cooked diced potato{300%g}, season with @salt and @pepper and fry, turning
occasionally, until golden brown and crispy, ~{8-9%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Halve the @lime{1/2}.

In a #large bowl{} mix together the @honey{15%g}, juice from half the lime and
@olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, season with @salt and @pepper and set aside.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

Pop the butter and half the @chipotle paste{20%g} into a #bowl{}, season with
@salt and @pepper and mix together until well combined.

> TIP: If your butter is too solid you can pop it in the microwave in a
> microwave proof bowl for 5-10 seconds until slightly softened.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Once hot, add the
@beef sizzler steaks{4}, season with @salt and @pepper and cook for
~{45%seconds} on each side.

> The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer the steaks to a plate and divide the chipotle butter
between them.

Stir the remaining chipotle through the potatoes and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

When everything else is ready, add the tomatoes and @wild rocket{40%g} to the
bowl with the dressing and toss together to coat.

Serve the potatoes, salad and any lime wedges (for squeezing over) alongside
the chipotle buttered steak and enjoy!